On July 20, 2018, the President signed three laws: the American Innovation $1 Coin Act, the North Korean Human Rights Reauthorization Act of 2017, and the reappointment of Barbara M. Barrett as a citizen regent of the Board of Regents of the Smithsonian Institution. The American Innovation $1 Coin Act requires the Department of the Treasury to mint coins in recognition of American innovation and the significant efforts of individuals or groups from each state, the District of Columbia, and US territories. The North Korean Human Rights Reauthorization Act of 2017 renews and amends the North Korean Human Rights Act of 2004. Lastly, Barbara M. Barrett was reappointed as a citizen regent of the Board of Regents of the Smithsonian Institution.